    <text>
        <body>
        	<div1 type="letter">
        		<pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0191"/>
        		<head>Jim to Mlle. Marcelle Guerin <date value="1915-10-16">October 16th ‘15</date></head>
        		
        		<opener>
            <dateline><date value="1915-10-16">October 16th ‘15</date></dateline>
        		</opener>
        		
            <p>
            One of our men is going to Paris
            so I’m sending in this note by
            him to be mailed from there.  Only
            a short note for I’m feeling rottenly [sic]
            and so want to walk around.
            I’ve contracted a world beating cold
            someplace or another.  A Hollander
            named Shroder nearly got it yesterday.
            Shell hit so close it slewed [sic]
            his car around but neither he
            nor his wounded man were hit.
            We’ve got a special run of luck
            someplace.
            </p><p>
            If you haven’t been able to locate
            an Outlook I can send you one.
            Landed an extra copy or two.  I
            haven’t heard from you for twenty
            one days now so don’t know 
            whether you have seen Paul or Outlooks
            or Salisbury or anything.  Hope you’re
            feeling well.  I’ve another recruit
            for aeronautic service named Haviland
            from U.S. Navy.  He’ll make a good
            one I think.  Haven’t you got a 
            little picture of yourself I might
            have?  Good luck, dear.
            </p>
        		
        		<closer>
            <signed>Jim</signed>
            
            <seg type="postscript">
            See you in about 5 weeks now.
            </seg>
        		</closer>
        		
        		<pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0192"/>
        		
            <!-- [The envelope with this letter is addressed to Mlle. Marcelle Guerin, 148 Bis Rue de Longchamp, Paris.] -->
            
